Russia Atomic Energy Agency to Aid Senegal Power, APS Says

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-02-11T09:46:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/russia-atomic-energy-agency-to-aid-senegal-power-aps-says.html
Russia’s Federal Atomic Energy
Agency will train Senegalese officials on nuclear energy, Agence
de Presse Senegalaise reported, citing a Foreign Affairs
Ministry  statement .  A Russian group will visit the West African nation for two
weeks in March that will include visits to  Senegal’s  current
energy-sector infrastructure, the Dakar-based news agency cited
the statement as saying. The two nations also discussed a
possible mining-industry agreement, the agency reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 